OL,3,CReform UK admits no viable route to
OL,4,Ctake control of Birmingham City Council
OL,6,FReform UK has admitted there is "no
OL,7,Fviable route" for the party to take
OL,8,Fcontrol of Birmingham City Council
OL,9,Fdespite emerging as the largest group
OL,10,Ffollowing last week's local elections.
OL,12,FThe party made major gains across the
OL,13,Fcity on Thursday, with Jex Parkin
OL,14,Felected in Kingstanding alongside
OL,15,Faround 22 other Reform UK councillors.
OL,17,FThe results left Reform as the biggest
OL,18,Fsingle party on the authority, but
OL,19,Fstill well short of the 51 seats
OL,20,Fneeded for an outright majority.
OL,26,@nD@aOUoD@MO]
