OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778746039
OL,3,CReform UK admits no viable route to
OL,4,Ctake control of Birmingham City Council
OL,6,FIn a statement issued after being
OL,7,Fselected as leader of the Reform UK
OL,8,Fgroup on the council, Parkin said
OL,9,Fvoters had delivered a clear message
OL,10,Fdemanding change.
OL,12,FHe said: "The results in Birmingham
OL,13,Fare historic. From a standing start,
OL,14,FReform UK is now the largest party on
OL,15,FBirmingham City Council. Voters are
OL,16,Fclearly demanding radical change.
OL,26,@tD@JOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778746039
OL,3,CReform UK admits no viable route to
OL,4,Ctake control of Birmingham City Council
OL,6,F"Although we are the largest party,
OL,7,Fother groups have made it clear that
OL,8,Fthey refuse to work with us, meaning
OL,9,Fthere is no viable route for Reform to
OL,10,Ftake control of the council.
OL,12,F"Given that Birmingham has also
OL,13,Fclearly elected a left-wing majority,
OL,14,Fwe have accepted that we will,
OL,15,Funfortunately, be unable to form an
OL,16,Fadministration.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778746039
OL,3,CReform UK admits no viable route to
OL,4,Ctake control of Birmingham City Council
OL,6,F"We are committed to being a
OL,7,Fconstructive opposition, ensuring the
OL,8,Fnew leadership is effectively
OL,9,Fscrutinised in order to get our city
OL,10,Fback on track."
OL,12,FThe Liberal Democrats and Greens had
OL,13,Falready ruled out working with Reform
OL,14,FUK in a coalition, leaving the party
OL,15,Fwithout a pathway to power at the
OL,16,Fcouncil.
OL,18,FEven with Conservative support, the
OL,19,Fnumbers would still fall short of a
OL,20,Fmajority in the council chamber.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@OO]
